<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-49-1079 </DOCNO><TEXT>A fierce international competition is under way, with our greatest traderivals devoting enormous resources to obtaining equality--if not eventualsuperiority--in biotechnology. Because biotechnology has diverse applicationsthat cut across many market sectors, including agriculture, pharmaceuticals,and chemicals, it is critical to our country's economic future. The biotechrace is one that the United States cannot afford to lose. Now is thereforethe time to develop a long term agenda and national strategy for biotechnology.We must show the foresight to protect our scientific know-how and theimagination to use it well. To ensure our competitive position, we mustdevelop a national biotechnology policy.</TEXT></DOC>